# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PyData London 2026 Workshop — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API key:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The notebooks auto-detect whichever provider variable is set, in this order:
#   NVIDIA_API_KEY  ->  OPENROUTER_API_KEY  ->  OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# Pick ONE provider; you do not need all three. Uncomment and fill in your key.
# Never commit .env -- it is gitignored.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# NVIDIA Build (recommended -- free tier on build.nvidia.com)
# NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-your-key-here

# OpenRouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-key-here

# OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# Where Data Designer caches model configs and run artifacts.
# Defaults to .data-designer/ inside the repo if unset.
# DATA_DESIGNER_HOME=.data-designer
